
This is a detailed technical explanation of the Fujian Fangda Weighing Apparatus weighbridge weighing monitoring system, focusing on **anti-cheating mechanisms** and **response speed optimization**, with explanations based on industry standards and cited references:
---
### I. Core Anti-Cheating Technology Implementation
#### 1. Anti-Interference Design of Digital Sensors
- **Signal Tampering Prevention**: Alloy steel digital sensors (such as 40CrNiMoA) are adopted to directly output **encrypted digital signals (AES-256)**, preventing interception and tampering by remote control devices during analog signal transmission.
- **Multi-Sensor Collaborative Monitoring**: The system compares data from \(n\) sensors in real time. If the deviation of the output value \(W_i\) of a certain sensor from the mean value \(\bar{W}\) of other sensors exceeds 0.1% (i.e., \( \left| \frac{W_i - \bar{W}}{\bar{W}} \right| > 0.001 \)), a positioning alarm is triggered immediately.
- **Environmental Interference Resistance**: The sensor has an IP68 sealing rating, and the internal temperature compensation circuit reduces creep error (full-scale creep error \( \leq 0.02\% \text{FS} \)), adapting to operating conditions from -10℃ to 50℃.

#### 2. Triple Data Anti-Counterfeiting System
```mermaid
graph TB
A[Sensor Data] --> B(Local Encrypted Storage)
B --> C[Video Overlay Verification]
C --> D{Cloud Blockchain Evidence Storage}
D --> E[ERP System Connection]
```
- **Video Overlay Tampering Prevention**: Images of vehicles and goods are captured at the moment of weighing, and data such as weight \(W\), time \(t\), and operator ID are **embedded into the image at the pixel level** to prevent post-modification.
- **Blockchain Evidence Storage**: A hash value \(H = \text{SHA-256}(W+t+\text{ID})\) is generated for key data and uploaded to the blockchain; any tampering will result in a hash mismatch (optional configuration).
- **Mandatory Process Locking**: The system executes in the sequence of "license plate recognition → tare weight → gross weight → printing", and data will be invalidated if any step is skipped.

#### 3. Physical-Level Protection
- **Infrared Positioning**: Infrared light curtains on both sides detect vehicle position, and weighing is refused if the vehicle is not fully on the scale (\( \text{Occlusion Rate} < 100\% \)).
- **RFID Goods Binding**: Integrated UHF RFID (e.g., UHF 860~960MHz) automatically associates goods ID with weight data to prevent cheating through goods replacement.
