### II. Response Speed Optimization Design
#### 1. Hardware-Level Acceleration
| **Component**       | **Traditional Solution**         | **Fangda Solution**               | **Speed Improvement Effect**       |
|---------------------|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Main Control Chip    | ARM Cortex-A7                    | Quad-Core Cortex-A53               | Computing Capacity \(\uparrow 200\%\) |
| AD Sampling Rate     | 80 times/sec                     | 200 times/sec                     | Sampling Delay \( \downarrow 60\% \) |
| Communication Protocol | RS485 (115.2kbps)              | CAN Bus (1Mbps)                   | Transmission Time \( \leq 500 \text{ms} \) |
| Watchdog Reset       | Software Trigger (≥2 sec)        | Hardware Monitoring (0.5 sec Forced Reboot) | System Crash Recovery \( \downarrow 75\% \) |

#### 2. Transmission and Processing Optimization
- **Dynamic Compression Transmission**: Weighing data is compressed via Huffman coding, with a single transmission volume satisfying:
  $$ \text{Compression Ratio} = \frac{\text{Original Data Volume}(2\text{KB})}{\text{Compressed Data Volume}(0.5\text{KB})} = 4 $$
  The response time is \( <1 \text{ second} \) under 4G networks.
- **Edge Computing**: Calibration compensation (such as nonlinear correction \( W_{\text{corrected}} = aW^2 + bW + c \)) is processed locally at the gateway to reduce reliance on the cloud.
